pageContext.claim: “They outspent me like five to one, only negative ads. You know, they're all negative. So by the time people got into the voter's booth, they only knew one thing...I think they spent like $2 billion dollars on negative ads. Everything was negative. So nobody knew what the hell she spent.”
pageContext.analysis: The Clinton campaign did not raise $2 billion much less spend that much on negative advertising.
